===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|holi|lang=enm}}, {{term|hali|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|halig|hāliġ|lang=ang}}, {{term|haleg|hāleġ|holy, consecrated, sacred, venerated, godly, saintly, ecclesiastical, pacific, tame|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|hailagaz|holy, bringing health|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Germanic|hailaz|healthy, whole|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|koil-|healthy, whole|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|haly||holy|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|heilig||holy|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|heilig||holy|lang=de}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|helig||holy|lang=sv}}. More at {{l|en|whole}}.

